other_tests.findings: Mild bilateral lower lobe dependent atelectasis, scattered coronary artery calcifications. The retrocecal appendix is dilated to 16 mm with surrounding fat stranding, mild wall thickening within the cecum along the base of the appendix. No free fluid or free air in the abdomen. Small pericecal lymph nodes do not meet CT size criteria. No pathologically enlarged abdominal lymph nodes.
